<section class="hero">
    <h1><em>Bitcoin</em> vs. The Stock Market</h1>
    <div class="hero-subtitle">What the historical record actually says about buying bitcoin at the worst possible moment &mdash; or every week through every cycle &mdash; versus the same in the S&amp;P 500, NASDAQ-100, or gold.</div>
    <p class="subtitle">If you&rsquo;ve never bought bitcoin and are weighing it against a normal index-fund portfolio, the question that gates the decision is some version of: <em>it&rsquo;s volatile and what if I buy in at exactly the wrong time?</em> The honest answer lives in the historical record. This page anchors on the five scariest scenarios &mdash; lump-sum purchases at the literal top of each bitcoin cycle, including the most recent one in October 2025 &mdash; and walks through what would have happened against the S&amp;P 500, NASDAQ-100, and gold over the years that followed. Then it extends the argument forward, using the Power Law trend to show how long the bitcoin advantage is likely to last for the typical investor&rsquo;s 10-to-15 year horizon.</p>
</section>

