                <h2>What if you bought at the worst time?</h2>
                <p><em>The fear-confronting scenario, anchored on each of the five major bitcoin cyclical tops.</em></p>
            </div>

            <p class="prose">The standard objection to buying bitcoin is some version of: <em>what if I buy in right before the crash?</em> The history of bitcoin includes several spectacular crashes &mdash; 80%+ drawdowns from the local top in late 2011, late 2013, late 2017, late 2021, the 2024 ATH&rsquo;s subsequent retracement, and the October 2025 all-time high that bitcoin remains roughly 35% below as of this writing. <strong>For someone considering an entry today, the relevant question isn&rsquo;t whether crashes happen &mdash; they do. It&rsquo;s what would have happened if you&rsquo;d been the unluckiest possible investor and bought at the literal top of each one.</strong></p>

            <p class="prose">The calculator below lets you pick a major cyclical top, an amount, and see what a lump-sum invested on that day would be worth today &mdash; against the same amount in the S&amp;P 500 (total return, with dividends reinvested), the NASDAQ-100 (total return), and gold (spot). The five anchored presets correspond to the local tops most likely to feature in a skeptical investor&rsquo;s memory &mdash; including the October 2025 all-time high, the most recent top and the one whose hold horizon is shortest.</p>

