            <p class="prose">For an investor with a typical decision horizon &mdash; 10 to 15 years &mdash; the Power Law trend keeps bitcoin meaningfully above all three comparators by a wide margin, with the gap measured in multiples rather than basis points. The convergence dates &mdash; where the Power Law trend eventually meets each comparator&rsquo;s trend line &mdash; sit far enough in the future that they&rsquo;re irrelevant to a typical investor&rsquo;s holding window. The relevant fact for someone deciding today isn&rsquo;t when the trend lines meet; <em>it&rsquo;s that they don&rsquo;t meet inside the horizon over which the typical investor actually holds.</em></p>
